THE PRESIDENT’S sudden talk of departure from a contested strip of the Turkey-Syria border betrays the Kurds who helped beat back Islamic State—and risks throwing the region into chaos. A look at the cashew industry in Mozambique reveals the tricky trade-offs between agriculture and development. And an unusual opera outlining the life and letters of birth-control pioneer Marie Stopes. Runtime: 20 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn